This article is the text of an executive order issued by President Barack Obama on July 6, 2012, titled "Assignment of National Security and Emergency Preparedness Communications Functions". The order emphasizes the importance of effective and resilient communication systems for the federal government to carry out critical missions and ensure national security. It establishes an NS/EP Communications Executive Committee to address communications matters and provides specific responsibilities for various government departments and agencies, including the Department of Defense, Department of Homeland Security, Department of Commerce, General Services Administration, and Federal Communications Commission. The order also outlines the general responsibilities of all agencies in relation to NS/EP communications. The executive order revokes previous orders and is subject to applicable law and available appropriations.